<TEXT>
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
urging an end to suspicions and the legacies of the past called 
wednesday for international cooperation on the environment space 
and afghanistan in a dramatic un speech punctuated by his pledge 
to reduce moscows troops 
gorbachev in an upbeat visit to new york that mixed business 
with tourism said presidentelect george bush will find in us a 
partner who is ready without long pause or backtracking to 
continue the dialogue in a spirit of realism openness and good 
will 
late wednesday a senior communist party official said gorbachev 
would cut short his trip to the united states and cancel his planned 
excursions to cuba and london to return home because of a 
devastating earthquake that struck the soviet caucasus region while 
the soviet leader was in new york a scientist in the capital of the 
republic of armenia estimated the death toll would run into 
thousands 
in his first address to the 159nation general assembly 
gorbachev also suggested the united nations deploy a peacekeeping 
force to afghanistan to oversee the withdrawal of soviet soldiers 
and the transition to a broadbased government he called for a jan 
1 ceasefire in the country 
gorbachev covered a range of topics and extolled peaceful 
coexistence in the world in his hourlong address he urged an end 
to cold war animosities 
after his speech gorbachev ate lunch with president reagan and 
bush on nearby governors island standing along a fence facing the 
statue of liberty gorbachev said the men had a good 
conversation 
later he and his wife raisa visited the world trade center 
where he thanked new yorkers for this warm hospitality dressed 
in a grey overcoat gorbachev said he hoped the superpowers would 
get rid as soon as we can of all suspicions and the legacies of 
the past 
asked if he pressed reagan for anything in return for his pledge 
to trim the soviet military by 500000 troops gorbachev said in 
developing our relations we can work only together so we do hope 
that the united states and the europeans will work with us and will 
take certain steps 
but the luncheon session was not a negotiating meeting 
gorbachev said adding he was happy to join reagan and bush in 
this gettogether 
it was the fifth meeting between reagan and gorbachev who was in 
washington a year ago to sign a treaty reducing intermediate and 
mediumrange missiles 
we are at the birth of a new model of ensuring security not 
through the buildup of arms but to the contrary through their 
reduction on the basis of compromise gorbachev said 
besides detailing troop reduction gorbachev outlined a number of 
proposals on a broad array of topics in his un speech 
he said for instance the soviet union is ready to impose a 
moratorium of up to century on debt servicing by poor countries and 
in some cases write off the debts 
he suggested an international space station monitor the 
environment and discussed having the international court of justice 
in the hague arbitrate human rights cases 
at home he said soviet democracy will be place on a solid 
normative basis with glasnost or openness and freedom of 
conscience enshrined in law 
members of the general assembly greeted gorbachev with sustained 
applause at the end of his 26page speech but they did not give him 
a standing ovation 
general assembly president dante caputo the foreign minister of 
argentina praised gorbachevs address as a very important speech 
with specific proposals on disarmament regional conflicts 
development and ecology he said it contained a new 
philosophical approach in soviet foreign policy 
gorbachev emphasized disarmament which he called the main 
issue and provided details of his unilateral initiatives to 
reduce the red armys strength 
today i can report to you that the soviet union has taken a 
decision to reduce its armed forces he said 
within the next two years their numerical strength will be 
reduced by 500000 men the numbers of conventional armaments will 
also be lsubstantially reduced this will be done unilaterally 
without relation to talks on conventional disarmament in vienna 
he said 
by agreement with the warsaw pact allies the soviet union will 
withdraw and disband six tank divisions from east germany 
czechoslovakia and hungary by 1991 
altogether he said soviet forces stationed in those three 
countries will be reduced by 50000 men some 5000 tanks will also 
be slashed he said 
the soviet union will also reorganize soviet divisions in eastern 
europe so they are clearly defensive 
gorbachev said the soviet union plans to cut soldiers and 
armaments in european part of his country and in its asian 
territory in mongolia for instance a major portion of soviet 
troops temporarily stationed there will return home he said 
but gorbachev warned we shall maintain our countrys defense 
capability at a level of reasonable and reliable sufficiency so 
that no one might be tempted to encroach on the security of the 
ussr and our allies 
turning to relations with the united states he said no one 
underestimates the seriousness of our differences and the 
toughness of outstanding problems 
but he said we have graduated from the primary school of 
learning to understand each other and seek solutions in our own and 
common interests 
the soviet union wants to work with the bush administration for 
consistent movement toward a treaty on 50 percent reduction in 
strategic offensive arms while preserving the antiballistic 
missile treaty he said 
</TEXT>
