the state elections commission had been recounting votes for this 
city of 1 million since the nov 8 general election 
in that voting puerto rico gov rafael hernandez colon of the 
popular democrats was reelected for a third term outgoing san juan 
mayor baltasar corrada del rio lost to colon 
city hall has been controlled since 1968 by the new progressive 
party which advocates statehood for the us commonwealth the 
popular democrats say they seek more autonomy in issues like trade 
and immigration but do not challenge the fundamental relationship 
with the united states 
