<TEXT>
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
claiming to have resolved his countrys human rights problems at 
home says the world court should have binding jurisdiction over 
enforcement of international human rights agreements 
in a wideranging address wednesday to the un general assembly 
the soviet leader called for vastly expanded responsibilities for 
the world body once shunned by his predecessors he also declared 
his government no longer holds political prisoners 
responding to western criticism of soviet emigration policy 
gorbachev said the kremlin has applied strict time limits on the use 
of state secrecy as a reason for refusing jews permission to 
emigrate 
although western observers generally acknowledge there have been 
dramatic reductions in the number of political prisoners since 
gorbachev rose to power human rights groups still count about 150 
people they say are being held solely because of their political or 
religious beliefs 
gorbachev said the problem of exit from and entry to our 
country including the question of leaving it for family 
reunification is being dealt with in a humane spirit but he gave 
no indication the soviet union is prepared to open its borders to 
unrestricted travel or emigration 
gorbachev also proposed a substantially broader role for the un 
and world organizations including the international court of 
justice at the hague netherlands commonly known as the world court 
the soviets have long promoted the concept of making the world 
courts humanrights rulings mandatory particularly on the five 
permanent members of the un security council the soviet union 
united states china britain and france 
the courts opinions now are advisory and nations tend to abide 
by them only when they so choose 
we believe that the jurisdiction of the international court of 
justice at the hague as regards the interpretation and 
implementation of agreements on human rights should be binding on 
all states gorbachev said 
our ideal is a world community of states which are based on the 
rule of law and which subordinate their foreign policy activities to 
law he said 
on the subject of soviet emigration policy one of gorbachevs 
closest advisers alexander yakovlev a member of the communist 
partys ruling politburo told an american peace coalition after the 
speech that he does not believe that there are any serious 
obstacles to those who want to emigrate 
he said the process of disarmament has not reached a stage at 
which it is possible to let those with military secrets leave the 
country but yakovlev contended there are fewer than 46 such cases 
remaining 
this is unfortunate he added but it is another motivation 
to disarm 
foreign ministry spokesman gennady i gerasimov said this is a 
problem that has disappeared with the establishment of an appeal 
procedure to permit review of refuseniks cases 
in his speech gorbachev also called for sending un 
peacekeepers into afghanistan and for barring weapons from outer 
space 
the soviet president proposed establishment of a peace corps 
to rebuild wartorn afghanistan and a team of international 
scientists to deal with environmental disasters 
turning from war on the ground to peace in the heavens gorbachev 
said the soviet union is also ready to cooperate in establishing 
an international space laboratory or manned orbital station designed 
exclusively for monitoring the state of the environment 
all activities in outer space must rule out the appearance of 
weapons there there is already a strongly felt need to develop 
an allembracing regime for peaceful work in outer space the 
verification of compliance with that regime would be entrusted to a 
world space organization an idea that the soviets have been 
promoting in the united nations for several years 
we are prepared to incorporate within its system our 
krasnoyarsk radar station in siberia he added the united states 
has claimed the facility violates the 1972 antiballistic missile 
treaty and must be dismantled 
gerasimov said wednesday all military personnel have been 
withdrawn from the radar station and there is no krasnoyarsk 
radar station any more 
soviet scientists gorbachev declared are prepared to 
receive their foreign colleagues and discuss with them ways of 
converting it into an international center for peaceful cooperation 
by dismantling and refitting certain units and structures and to 
provide additional equipment the entire system could function under 
the auspices of the united nations 
a major function of the space laboratory would be to keep track 
of pollution for which gorbachev had another proposal 
let us also think about setting up within the framework of the 
united nations a center for emergency environmental assistance its 
function would be promptly to send international groups of experts 
to areas with badly deteriorating environment he said 
developing nations have been crushed by debt repayment schedules 
during the 1980s the total third world debt is over 12 trillion 
and many nations cant even pay the interest on their loans 
gorbachev proposed limiting their official debtservicing 
payments depending on the economic performance of each of them or 
granting them a long period of deferral in the repayment of a major 
portion of their debt 
he offered a moratorium on debt service of up to 100 years for 
the most needy debtor nations 
he backed the appeal of the genevabased un conference on trade 
and development for reducing debts owed to commercial banks which 
are almost exclusively in western nations 
</TEXT>
