women who accept a 725 compensation offer for 
injuries caused by dalkon shield birthcontrol devices may be giving 
up claims worth many times that amount according to representatives 
of organizations that support these victims 
weve waited for years and we urge women to take the time now 
to make a careful decision about this first offer nancy worth 
davis of the dalkon shield oversight consortium told a news 
conference on wednesday 
nearly 200000 women have filed claims of dalkon shieldrelated 
injuries ranging from infections to sterility miscarriage and 
children born with birth defects 
us district judge robert merhige of richmond va has approved 
a 24 billion trust fund for women injured by the birth control 
device on dec 5 the administrators of the trust fund sent letters 
to women who used the shields offering them 725 to settle all 
claims as option 1 
the letter makes clear that it is only for women whose injuries 
are less severe or have very little if any proof to support their 
claim and who feel that 725 is fair and adequate compensation a 
separate option 1 will be offered to those who claim injury 
because of someone elses use such as the husbands or children of 
users 
other options not yet available will address more serious and 
specific injuries 
ms davis said this letter does not tell women what they are 
giving up in exchange for the 725 that it asks women to take the 
first offering is a throwaway offering 
this letter is for women who were not seriously injured women 
who have minimal claims or women who may have worn a shield for a 
couple of months and suffered from it and removed it immediately 
she said 
the ah robins co which manufactured the dalkon shield 
declared bankruptcy three years ago last july american home 
products corp agreed to buy the company and set up a trust fund to 
compensate the claimants 
sybil shainwald of health action international said there were 
17 million foreign users of the device and many of them are still 
wearing this time bomb in their bodies since no adequate recall 
campaign has ever been undertaken by robins or by any government 
robins spent 45 million in the us and approximately 
500000 outside the us to notify women of their rights an 
obvious discrimination at the time against foreign women women 
throughout the world were the guinea pigs for an unsafe and untested 
birth control device they paid with their wombs and their lives 
she said women should remember this is not a final offer but 
an elimination process 
several women at the news conference objected to the judges 
recent removal of the female chairman and two of the trustees 
supervising the trust 
merhige removed the trustees nov 28 after a complaint that they 
had shown bad judgment resulting in inaction and delays there were 
