nato foreign ministers today called for 
substantial reductions in conventional forces in europe as part of 
their negotiating position at upcoming arms talks 
the nato position intended to cover western and soviet bloc 
forces was released one day after soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev said he would unilaterally cut the soviet armed forces by 
500000 troops including 50000 in the east bloc 
secretary of state george p shultz also met with nato members 
today to try to persuade them to insist on further cutbacks in 
soviet troops 
in a statement today the nato ministers said they will propose 
an overall limit on the total number of arms in europe 
this limit should be substantially lower than existing levels 
in the case of tanks close to half it said this would mean an 
overall limit of about 40000 tanks 
in the statement the allies also said no country should be 
allowed to have more than a fixed proportion such as 30 percent of 
total arms in europe such a formula it said would set a cap of no 
more than about 12000 tanks for any one country 
it also said nato negotiators would propose limits on forces 
stationed in other countries territory 
the statement said the allies position would apply to all of 
europe 
in order to avoid undue concentration of these weapon 
categories in certain areas of europe we shall propose appropriate 
sublimits it said 
the allies position will be offered at the conventional 
stability talks scheduled to get under way early next year in 
vienna austria 
