<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on armenia the southern soviet 
republic where a devastating earthquake killed thousands of people 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land armenia is a mountainous republic covering 11490 
square miles an area similar in size to the state maryland it is 
bordered by turkey on the west the georgian soviet republic to the 
north and the azerbaijan soviet republic to the east to the south 
lie iran and the soviet republic of nakhichevan the capital of 
armenia is yerevan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people the population is 33 million about 90 percent 
armenian most of whom are christian about 5 percent are 
azerbaijani 23 percent russian and 17 percent kurd 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy mining is an important industry and armenia has 
large deposits of metals and minerals other industries are 
chemicals textiles and winemaking 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history armenia was proclaimed a soviet socialist republic on 
nov 29 1920 in february armenians began agitating for annexation 
of the armenian enclave of nagornokarabakh a mountainous region in 
azerbaijan the protest caused antiarmenian riots in cities in 
predominantly moslem azerbaijan and so far the unrest has resulted 
in about 60 confirmed deaths 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

