<TEXT>
ulanhu vice chairman of the national peoples 
congress who fought for native mongolian rights during his more than 
60year political career died thursday he was 82 
ulanhu died in beijing after being hospitalized for an 
unspecified illness the official xinhua news agency said 
he worked for inner mongolias independence from 
nationalistruled china in the 1930s and also fought japanese 
efforts to occupy inner mongolia he also served as personal 
secretary to a chinese warlord in the region and did underground 
work for the chinese communist party 
after the partys victory in 1949 ulanhu held a series of posts 
in the central government including vice premier 
he also was appointed government chairman party secretary and 
army commander in inner mongolia and ruled the vast barren region 
virtually singlehandedly for nearly two decades before being 
toppled in 1967 during the cultural revolution 
as inner mongolias top official ulanhu urged chinas majority 
han nationality to respect the rights of the countrys minorities 
including the mongols 
when radical youth groups called red guards tried to take over 
inner mongolian government offices in 1967 ulanhu used his troops 
against them leftist leaders in beijing finally sent in outside 
troops to remove ulanhu from office on charges of having made 
himself ruler in an independent kingdom 
ulanhus supporters in inner mongolia fought the outside troops 
for months calling themselves the genghis khan combat corps in 
honor of the 13th century mongolian general who conquered much of 
central asia including parts of china 
after being rehabilitated in 1973 ulanhu held posts in the 
partys top policymaking bodies the central committee and the 
politburo but was never returned to office in inner mongolia he 
also led numerous delegations overseas in the late 1970s 
he has served as a vice chairman on the national peoples 
congress the legislature since 1975 currently there are 18 other 
vice chairmen 
he retired last year at the 13th national party congress 
ulanhu was a longtested veteran communist an outstanding 
party and state leader and a proletarian revolutionary as well as a 
noted guide of minoritynationality affairs said xinhua quoting 
an obituary issued by the party 
he was born in 1906 in inner mongolia to an aristocratic family 
he was educated in moscow and beijing where he joined the communist 
youth league in 1923 and the communist party soon after 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

