<TEXT>
here is the text of the comments of mikhail s 
gorbachev as spoken by his translator at john f kennedy 
international airport prior to his departure for the soviet union on 
thursday 
i would like to say that i have to cut short this visit and to 
return to the soviet union because late last night it was reported 
to me that the earthquake that struck the transcaucasian republics 
of the soviet union and particularly armenia was extremely severe 
and had extremely grave consequences devastation and grave loss of 
life i urgently have to return to the soviet union 
at present a government commission is already at work headed 
by the prime minister of the soviet union it is already in the 
disaster area urgent measures are being taken to help all those 
affected by this terrible tragedy and i have to be there in this 
effort 
this morning i had telephone conversations with president 
reagan and vice president bush both of them expressed profound 
condolences on behalf of the american people to those affected and 
to the government and people of the soviet union i thanked them for 
the expression of those feelings and let me say here again on 
behalf of myself of the soviet people and on behalf of those to 
whom those feelings of sympathy were expressed by the president and 
the vice president let me extend our deep gratitud and our profound 
appreciation 
the president and the vice president conveyed their willingness 
to extend assistance and appropriate help in this situation i would 
like to thank them and i would like to thank the american people 
for those feelings and for their readiness to give assistance in 
this difficult hour 
it has so happened that we had only one working day here in new 
york but i and my delegation believe that this was a very important 
day we were able to set out our views at the united nations on the 
world today and on the prospects of the worlds development we did 
that at the united nations an organization which we value very 
highly and whose role we believe will grow in the development of 
new international relations 
we also were able to have another of the useful exchanges at 
the united nations to talk to representatives of many countries 
and we feel that they understand what we said at the united nations 
yesterday i had the meeting with president reagan and vice 
president the presidentelect george bush and members of the 
current and future us administrations we and the american side 
share the view that this was a very important meeting which has 
confirmed the high level of sovietamerican relations which makes 
it possible to discuss very important questions affecting relations 
between our countries and problems of improving international 
relations 
this was a good meeting held in a very good atmosphere an open 
and trusting atmosphere we believe that it was characterized by a 
readiness to understand the positions of each other and yesterday 
when i was asked to describe in one word the essence and the main 
motive of that meeting i said that word was continuity 
so that meeting yesterday and the telephone conversations that 
we had today when we also briefly addressed our future cooperation 
make us confident make the soviet union and the united states 
confident that our relations will expand and improve on the basis 
of cooperation on the basis of mutual respect for each others 
interests and also taking into account responsibilities for our 
nations and for the world 
i think i would remiss in my duty if i went home without saying 
how much we are grateful to new yorkers for the hospitality and 
feelings of friendship that they have been expressing over these 
days so to all new yorkers our very warm gratitude we value that 
very much we believe that this may have been one of the most 
important things that happened on this day of our stay in america 
that shows increased and increasing respect and friendliness and 
willingness to cooperate on the part of the soviet people and the 
american people 
the road ahead will be tough but we will go ahead and we will 
i believe be building on what has been achieved if we act as we 
have been acting and also maybe add something new i think that 
would open up good prospects for our two peoples and will be 
extremely important for the world as well 
goodbye and thank you 
</TEXT>
