<TEXT>
from the days president george washington 
dispatched the first united states marshals to quell the whiskey 
rebellion the storied lawmen have been part of the countrys most 
colorful and most violent episodes 
they did the hanging for famous hanging judge isaac parker of 
fort smith ark after rounding up bank and train robbers hiding in 
the brush of indian territory smashed whiskey stills during 
prohibition and protected slaves freed after the civil war 
the nations oldest law enforcement organization the marshals 
began their bicentennial celebration thursday with the opening of an 
exhibit at the supreme court followed by a blacktie dinner at a 
nearby hotel 
organized by the marshals service with the help of the 
smithsonian insitution the exhibit displays artifacts from 
massacres and shootouts that have earned the men their place in the 
lore of the wild west and their immortalization by movie legends 
john wayne and henry fonda 
as the united states expanded across the continent us 
marshals and their deputies established the federal goverments 
authority over areas that had known little order and no goverment 
most of them were rough uncouth men according to an excerpt of 
the marshals official history by frederick s calhoun 
the brothers of deputy frank dalton one of many men killed in 
indian territory were also deputies before they turned to robbing 
banks 
they were the federal goverment at the local level calhoun 
said there was no infrastructure of a bureaucracy so when the 
citizens got mad they took it out on the federal marshals 
as a result as many as 100 marshals and their deputies died in 
indian territory between 1872 and 1896 their deadliest era calhoun 
said 
with the exception of indian territory the far most dangerous 
time to be a marshal was in the south after the civil war calhoun 
said if the ku klux klan didnt get you the moonshiners did 
at least 400 and as many as 700 marshals have died in the line of 
duty more than any other law enforcement agency but the exact 
number isnt known because of difficulties in determining whether 
members of posses had actually been deputized before their deaths 
said marshals service director stanley morris 
at almost every point in history when the federal government 
was involved in a significant event there were marshals 
participating said marshals service spokesman stephen boyle 
a marshal who fired the gun that sent settlers scrambling for a 
homestead in the oklahoma land run of 1889 at guthrie marshals 
guarded the first black student at the university of 
mississippioxford in the 1960s and marshals ringed the pentagon 
during the vietnam war protests of the early 1970s 
they arrested gangster al capone twice and took the census until 
1880 
as evidence of those events the marshals exhibit contains the 
arrest warrant for geronimo an 1870 ku klux klan robe and hood from 
a recruit in the klans birthpace of pulaski tenn a 1790 whiskey 
still from the whiskey rebellion era and one of the two machine 
guns from the st valentines day massacre in chicago the 
bloodiest of prohibition 
the exhibit which will tour a dozen cities over the next 2 
years also includes a jesse james vest and sidearm and original 
drawings by wyatt earp of four gunfights including one at the ok 
corral involving the legendary wild west marshal 
appointed by the president the 94 district us marshals are a 
part of the executive branch created by the first congress in the 
judiciary act of 1789 the same law that established the supreme 
court and the federal judicial system 
the marshals of the 1980s provide security in federal court and 
protect supreme court justices when they travel beyond washington 
they operate the witness protection program that gives new 
identities to those whose lives are jeopardized by testifying for 
the government and track down federal fugitives 
they also take custody of those accused of federal crimes and 
transport federal prisoners running the governments only scheduled 
airline service with two boeing 727s and smaller aircraft out of 
their oklahoma city hub morris said 
they are responsible for property seized in the war on drugs and 
other federal crimes and have managed horse ranches restaurants 
condominums a golf course and a greenhouse 
with just 3000 employees the service is smaller than the new 
york city police department morris said yet its ranks are 
stationed in every us judicial district from guam to the virgin 
islands 
</TEXT>
