the environmental protection agency said 
thursday its bringing more lawsuits than ever 
in the 1988 fiscal year that ended sept 30 the agency turned 
over 372 civil cases to the justice department compared with the 
previous record of 342 civil cases in the 1986 fiscal year there 
were 59 criminal cases in fiscal 1988 compared with 41 in both 1986 
and 1987 
however the agencys administrative orders totaled 3085 down 
slightly from 3194 in the previous year epa said it tried not to 
issue a large number of orders when new school asbestos regulations 
took effect at the start of the year but rather tried to make sure 
school boards understood them 
the agency said state environmental agencies referred 904 civil 
cases to their attorneys general and issued 9363 administrative 
orders both figures were said to be records but the old records 
were not given 
