from contracts because of certain air or water pollution violations 
compared with three in january 1986 and had 450 judicial consent 
decrees in effect compared with 200 in 1984 
though the justice department is free to reject cases sent to it 
by epa epa spokeswoman robin woods said the department accepts 
virtually all of them 
