teachers credential honig said 
major colleges and universities in california are accredited 
through recognized national or regional academicstandards groups 
smaller schools such as technical or business colleges require 
approval from the state school superintendent to grant degrees 
in 1986 the legislature and governor tightened the states 
credentialing laws requiring numerous small schools including the 
institute for creation research to apply to the state for permission 
to grant degrees 
