made known he told a news conference that he took no part in the 
dealings and had no knowledge about the unlisted shares of the real 
estate company 
later an investigation by the japan communist party showed that 
miyazawa bought 10000 unlisted shares of recruit cosmos in 
september 1986 and earned more than 164000 in profits by selling 
them immediately after the company went public a month later 
after that happened he told the committee that his former aide 
bought shares from his business associate without his knowledge 
it was disclosed in a parliamentary investigation last month that 
the aide tsuneo hattori bought shares directly from recruit inc 
the real estate firms parent company 
