<TEXT>
all three measures of the nations money supply 
rose in late november the federal reserve board reported thursday 
the fed said the narrowest measure of the money supply m1 rose 
31 billion to a seasonally adjusted 7878 billion in the week 
ended nov 28 from 7847 billion the previous week 
the central bank said a broader measures known as m2 rose 37 
billion to a seasonally adjusted 30619 billion from 30582 
billion the previous week 
an even broader measure m3 increased 19 billion to a 
seasonally adjusted 38967 billion from 38948 billion 
m1 includes cash in circulation deposits in checking accounts 
and nonbank travelers checks m2 is m1 plus accounts like savings 
deposits and moneymarket mutual funds m3 is m2 plus lessliquid 
accounts such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations 
of 100000 
in judging its monetary policy the fed has indicated it is 
monitoring the value of the dollar commodity prices and the 
difference between short and longterm interest rates as well as 
the broader money measures m2 and m3 
in other reports 
the federal reserve said bank borrowings from the federal 
reserve system at the discount window averaged 558 million in the 
latest week down from 1104 billion in the previous week 
the federal reserve bank of st louis reported that the monetary 
base the seasonally adjusted total of member bank reserves held at 
federal reserve banks and cash in bank vaults and in circulation 
was 2857 billion in the twoweek period ended wednesday up from 
2850 billion two weeks earlier 
