<TEXT>
a jury on thursday found that pillsbury co 
sustained nearly 50 million in losses in 1984 to 1986 due to 
publicity regarding use of the pesticide ethylenedibromide better 
known as edb pillsbury said 
the hennepin county district court jurys decision is the result 
of claims by pillsbury against five insurance companies seeking 
restitution for its losses the case involves a 150 million 
insurance policy issued by national union fire insurance co royal 
indemnity co employers mutual casualty co home insurance co and 
federal insurance co as well as a sixth company now in insolvency 
proceedings 
lawyers for the insurance companies could not immediately be 
reached for comment 
the policy issued to pillsbury in 1983 was designed to protect 
food companies against losses such as those due to publicity 
surrounding the discovery of potentially toxic materials in a food 
product 
